<TEXT>
matthew stuart who exposed his late brothers 
plot to kill his pregnant wife was called friday before a grand 
jury investigating the slaying 
stuart was seen leaving the office used by the grand jury but 
his attorney nancy gertner refused to say if he had testified 
the case drew widespread attention when it broke dramatically 
the night of oct 23 a frantic charles stuart called police on his 
car phone to say his pregnant wife carol had been shot by a 
robber 
police found the middleclass couple in their car in an inner 
city neighborhood near a hospital where they had attended a 
birthing class mrs stuart was fatally wounded and stuart himself 
had a serious gunshot wound the baby delivered prematurely died 
17 days later 
for days nobody doubted stuarts story that the family had been 
attacked by a black mugger 
matthew stuart provided a dramatic turnaround in the case jan 
3 when he told authorities his brother had arranged for him to be 
at the murder scene 
he also told investigators he helped dispose of a gun which 
turned out to be the murder weapon 
charles stuart committed suicide jan 4 after his brother 
implicated him in the crime 
yet matthew stuarts revelations also raised questions about his 
role in the plot he has insisted he had no prior knowledge that 
mrs stuart would be killed and he said he did not see her body in 
the couples car when charles stuart passed him the handbag that 
contained the gun 
since stuarts suicide a suffolk county grand jury has convened 
periodically to piece together details of the plot prosecutors 
have not said whether charges might be filed 
matthew stuart arrived at the suffolk county district attorneys 
office friday morning he was seen with his two sisters but 
gertner indicated they were only accompanying him to the 
courthouse both sisters already have appeared before the grand 
jury 
i cant tell you whats happening gertner said 
everything before the grand jury has been impounded all the 
motions that have been filed are impounded 
</TEXT>
