<TEXT>
with disclosure of past drug use a possible 
complication president bushs nominee to regulate the nations 
savings and loans faces a confirmation fight on the senate floor 
next week 
by an 1110 vote friday t timothy ryan jr barely won the 
endorsement of the senate banking committee to become director of 
the treasury departments office of thrift supervision 
the drug issue did not arise in the committee meeting but hours 
later after an nbc news report the administration confirmed that 
the 44yearold attorney told fbi background investigators that he 
used marijuana and cocaine on a few occasions in the early 1970s 
treasury secretary nicholas f brady said the administration 
knew of ryans admission and that the senate committee had voted 
in full knowledge of these same facts he said ryan still had 
the administrations confidence 
nbc said some senators were privately troubled by ryans past 
drug use although none raised the issue publicly 
two democrats joined the committees nine republicans in backing 
ryan ten democrats opposed him complaining he had no experience 
in banking 
sorting through the aftermath of the savings and loan collapse 
will be the single most demanding and difficult financial job in 
our country so obviously we want someone of a towering size and 
capacity to tackle that assignment said the panels chairman 
sen donald w riegle jr who opposed the nomination 
nevertheless riegle dmich said he hoped the full senate 
could act swiftly on the nomination perhaps on wednesday the day 
after senators are expected to complete a clean air bill 
the administration has been under pressure to appoint a thrift 
director since march 21 when a federal judge ruled the agency 
lacked constitutional authority to seize troubled institutions 
the us court of appeals has delayed the ruling until april 11 
and the administration wants a senateconfirmed thrift director in 
office before then 
ryan an attorney who specializes in pension and employee 
benefit law would replace m danny wall who resigned under fire 
for his handling of the collapse of lincoln savings and loan 
association of irvine calif 
following the nbc report ryan issued a statement saying 
prior to my nomination i disclosed both on my fbi form and 
verbally to the white house treasury and the fbi that early in the 
1970s i smoked marijuana on a few occasions and tried cocaine once 
perhaps twice 
i regret this mistake i do not regret having voluntarily 
disclosed this information he said 
treasury secretary brady said in his own statement the 
incidents were limited and a long time ago we knew about this 
issue because the nominee voluntarily disclosed this information 
we believe mr ryan is well qualified and his nomination deserves 
the senates full support 
democrats said ryans inexperience in the sampl field would force 
him to rely on guidance from the treasury department rather than 
exercise independent judgment they complained he had no opinion on 
such basic issues as financial standards for sampls and whether the 
thrift industry has a future 
the administration countered by portraying ryan as an 
experienced manager and tough enforcer who as solicitor of the 
labor department from 1981 to 1983 supervised 600 attorneys and 
helped clean up corruption in the teamsters unions central states 
pension fund 
sen jake garn of utah the senior republican on the committee 
conceded that ryan lacked experience but argued that 
conflictofinterest rules and postemployment restrictions have 
grown so tight that the administration had a very difficult time 
finding a candidate with more relevant qualifications 
we may reach a point where mother teresa is the only person we 
can confirm to any position in the federal government garn said 
riegle had predicted thursday evening that his panel would 
reject ryan but several members said brady made impassioned pleas 
on the nominees behalf 
democratic sens terry sanford of north carolina and richard 
shelby of alabama ended up joining republicans in support of the 
nomination 
sanford told reporters ryan was a personal friend whom he knew 
through the american council of young political leaders 
shelby who said he was prepared to vote against ryan as late as 
thursday night said friday that he thought the full senate should 
have a chance to vote adding the job needs to be filled 
in addition to his labor department service ryan has extensive 
political experience he served in the presidential campaigns of 
richard nixon in 1972 gerald ford in 1976 and george bush in 1988 
he was a legal counsel to ronald reagans 1980 transition team 
