at issue is the largescale retail store law a prime target of 
us trade pressure under the law local shopkeepers many fearful 
of the competition that a larger and likely lowerpriced 
supermarket or department store would bring often can stop a 
competitor from moving into their area 
in a news release the chains chairman nobutsugu shimizu said 
it was a shame to the country and its people to maintain such a 
law 
retailers in shiki city 15 miles north of tokyo are against 
the disputed supermarket because they fear their businesses will be 
damaged said eiten sato a spokesman for the shiki chamber of 
commerce 
under the law the ministry of international trade and industry 
can require large retailers to obtain local approval if their store 
is likely to negatively affect local retailers without approval 
large retailers cannot open new outlets 
the store law is a focal point in usjapanese trade talks 
which are to resume monday in washington the united states says 
the law gives undue influence to japanese manufacturers and 
prevents imported products from reaching store shelves 
in contrast japanese retailers such as mitsukoshi and tokyu 
department stores and yaohan supermarkets have already opened 
stores in the united states 
in a test of trade barriers the government agreed tuesday to 
consider a request by us toy retailer toys r us inc to open a 
53000squarefoot discount store in the country 
us officials says the loosening of japans market could ease a 
us trade deficit with japan that reached 49 billion last year 
however the trade and industry minister kabun muto said 
earlier this week that he has no intention of scrapping the law 
life stores an osakabased grocery store chain with 70 branches 
nationwide is also requesting the immediate ban of the law store 
chairman shimizu said he might drop the suit if the government 
agrees to scrap the law in the trade talks with us officials 
he said life stores action came shortly before the 
usjapanese meeting because we thought its now or never 
victims of the largescale store law are none other than the 
consumers shimizu said 
</TEXT>
