affluent families 
youll notice a lack of the wagging of tongues on this 
issue downey said it was not a topic of debate there was 
fulsome recognition of the reality that middle class people needed 
to be taken care of and the way to do that was the 
afterschool program 
the revenue recovered by cutting the credit is relatively small 
the congressional budget office put the amount at 15 billion over 
five years sponsors came up with another 13 billion by extending 
the telephone excise tax but even with that the bill would add to 
the federal deficit 
