the expenses of special care for other dependents such as an 
infirm parent or disabled spouse or older child 
and it affects currently untaxed employer benefits she said 
for people above the cutoff level employeroffered child care 
programs at free or reduced cost will become a taxable benefit 
eliminating the credit has been attempted before house 
democrats included it in the 1988 welfare reform bill but it was 
eliminated in the senate where sen bill bradley dnj attacked 
the move as robbing jill to pay jane 
