quality of life said keane 
a decade ago 75 percent of the people who received forms in the 
mail completed them and sent them back 
the country is bigger and more complex today the bureau is 
hoping to get back 70 percent this time 
sending workers out to find people who dont respond costs 
taxpayers 10 million for each 1 percent 
yet the bureau is determined to come as close as possible to 
counting everyone 
we are prepared to chase and chase and chase again said 
bryant 
but while the count is getting lots of attention right now 
