overthrew 45 years of communist dictatorship 
thousands of flagwaving people accompanied by soldiers in 
parade uniform staged an officially sanctioned march through 
downtown bucharest they passed makeshift candlelit shrines along 
the streets and in squares marking spots where some of the fiercest 
fighting took place 
the march started at a cathedral in front of parliament where 
services were held president ion iliescu and premier petre roman 
were there to join worshipers 
after leaving the prayer services some marchers walked to 
heroes cemetery at the outskirts of the capital where several 
hundred people killed in the fierce street battles between 
prodemocracy demonstrators and security agents are buried 
