largescale demonstrations against the regime of former dictator 
nicolae ceausescu first broke out in the western city of timisoara 
on dec 16 but soon spread to other parts of the country 
on dec 22 1989 ceausescu and his wife elena fled the 
capital where street fighting had broken out between secret police 
loyal to his regime and the army which sided with hundreds of 
thousands of demonstrators demanding an end to four decades of 
communist rule 
ceausescu and his wife were quickly apprehended and later 
executed on dec 25 
