helen hoke watts the author and publisher of 
childrens books has died at the age of 86 
mrs watts died of pneumonia at a nursing home near her 
residence in the washington suburb of chevy chase md 
her works included the horse that took the milk around and 
too many kittens and the series witches witches witches 
jokes jokes jokes and nurses nurses nurses 
she wrote a number of anthologies reflecting her interest in 
ghost stories the supernatural and witchcraft 
born in california pa mrs watts worked as a journalist and 
teacher before moving to the state of california in 1929 in 1936 
she moved to new york 
in addition to writing she managed childrens books departments 
for new york publishers she served as vice president and director 
of international projects for franklin watts inc publishers a 
company formed by her second husband 
she later lived in london and again in new york before moving to 
the washington areas 
mrs watts who died monday is survived by a son john hoke of 
bethesda md four grandchildren 
