area have resisted ganienkeh a suggestion that someone outside 
the encampment may have fired the shots to discredit the mohawks 
when cuomo was new yorks secretary of state in 1977 he helped 
negotiate an end to a threeyear occupation by mohawks of land at 
moss lake about 100 miles southwest of altona that agreement led 
to the creation of the ganienkeh encampment where about 40 mohawks 
live on 700 acres 
the mohawks claimed the camp was among 9 million acres in new 
york and vermont wrongfully taken from them in the 18th century 
fifteen years ago a 22yearold man and a 9yearold girl were 
shot and wounded while riding in cars near another ganienkeh 
encampment and the indians also refused to cooperate no one was 
ever charged 
the mohawks at ganienkeh which means land of the flint say 
they are trying to protect ancient mohawk traditions and culture by 
living in a community that does not accept aid from federal state 
or county governments 
whites are not allowed onto the core of the settlement though 
ganienkeh spokesmen said the bingo hall was opened in 1988 as a 
means of raising money to build roads a clinic and make other 
community improvements 
mohawks have ignored restraining orders secured by new york 
state authorities to close the 1400seat bingo hall 
