discrimination and police raids on drinking clubs and suspected 
drug users 
saturdays london violence was the worst since september 1985 
when crowds of young blacks and some whites clashed with police in 
the northern industrial city of birmingham two ugandanborn 
brothers died there when their post office was burnt out 
