a landslidedamaged petroleum pipeline sent 
an 8milelong slick down the allegheny river on saturday 
threatening water supplies for more than 100000 people 
authorities said 
fumes from the spill forced the evacuation of 100 people 
heavy rain friday apparently caused the landslide that cracked 
the pipeline the same day said ray haase jr of buckeye pipeline 
