<TEXT>
brazils cost of living rose 84 
percent in march its highest monthly increase ever the government 
said friday 
march inflation easily topped februarys rate of 73 percent 
according to the official brazilian geography and statistics 
institute 
inflation has increased 397 percent since january and 4853 
percent over the last 12 months the institute reported 
the march rate calculated from midfebruary to midmarch 
reflected the wild surge in prices preceding the inauguration of 
president fernando collor de mello sworn in march 15 for a 
fiveyear term in this country of 150 million residents 
transportation and communications pushed up the cost of living 
more than any other item jumping 9483 percent during the 30day 
period personal items soared 9237 percent and food 8415 percent 
the institute reported 
collor brazils first popularly elected leader since 1960 
announced the countrys fifth and most radical antiinflation 
package a day after taking office 
price controls a new currency a de facto devaluation and a 
crackdown on financial speculators were included in the plan 
but the backbone of the package a severe tightening of the 
money supply hikes in taxes and utilities and a freeze on bank 
deposits that totaled 115 billion have prompted mass layoffs and 
fears of recession 
workers unions estimate more than 200000 brazilians have 
already lost their jobs in rio alone 11000 people have been laid 
off the last 13 days 
retailers have been offering easy credit and discounts as high 
as 80 percent to entice cashstrapped brazilians to buy goods 
some clothing stores are selling merchandise by the pound car 
dealers are bartering vehicules for rice and coffee and 
supermarkets are now accepting credit cards 
</TEXT>
