injury care manager program to coordinate services 
the national head injury foundation calls head trauma a silent 
epidemic 
jerry lewis isnt out there pushing for head injury 
children said dr samuel kasoff chairman of the neurosurgery 
department at westchester county medical center in valhalla 
the foundation estimates that more than a million people suffer 
some degree of head trauma each year some 100000 die from their 
injuries of those that survive 70000 to 90000 are left with 
impairments that prevent them from living normal lives 
motor vehicle accidents account for more than half the head 
injuries according to the nhif twenty percent are caused by 
falls 12 percent by violence and 10 percent are suffered during 
sports or recreation activities 
increased use of helmets and seat belts and better emergency 
medical treatment have resulted in more people surviving head 
injuries said trauma surgeon john b fortune 
were a mechanized mobile society we go very fast and get 
into accidents unfortunately one of the organs that gets injured 
a lot is the head said fortune director of the northeastern new 
york regional trauma center at albany medical center hospital 
with more survivors demand grew in the 1980s for rehabilitation 
ten years ago when we were formed there were about five rehab 
facilities like new medico now there are about 600 said silvana 
guercilena spokeswoman for the nhif a southborough massbased 
advocacy group 
for victims of severe head injury rehabilitation can be long 
and painful with no guarantees 
when been arrived at new medico on sept 1 1988 six weeks 
after a car accident he could not walk or talk he suffered memory 
loss and became easily distracted and agitated common symptoms of 
traumatic brain injury 
theres parts of my life i dont remember he said its 
hard i used to cry a lot then i make the best of what it is and 
say thanks lets go on 
about 50 head injury patients ages 16 and older occupy new 
medicos two floors said spokeswoman kathryn rockenstire a nearby 
center opened in 1989 and specializes in treating children 
with 38 facilities nationwide new medico is the nations 
largest provider of head injury rehabilitation costs start at 375 
per day and go as high as 950 per day depending on the extent of 
the rehab program considering the average stay at new medico is 
seven months the total could reach 199500 
a lot of people cant even get into these facilities because 
their insurance doesnt cover them to be there said guercilena 
their insurance covers them to be in a nursing home for the rest 
of their lives 
there are less expensive facilities new medicos rehab centers 
stress gracious living rockenstire said at troy english 
hunting prints and oriental art decorate the walls visitors sit in 
thick leather chairs and sofas in the lobby in a lounge decorated 
with queen anne furniture coffee is offered from a silver serving 
set 
new medicos philosophy to give it a home atmosphere not an 
institution rockenstire said we want this to be a place where 
family members can feel comfortable 
the goal of head injury rehabilitation is to get the patient 
back home back to work and contributing to society though he was 
looking forward to going home been kept his excitement in check 
he knows the bitterness of setbacks 
been whose insurance paid for his new medico stay was 
discharged last month and has returned home to the bronx with his 
wife rockenstire said he has the potential to return to work but 
will need retraining and rehabilitation she said 
before the accident been was a 24yearold security guard none 
of the three other people in the car suffered a scratch 
i didnt even break a nail been said i said to my wife 
later honey didnt i even break something 
five months after he arrived at new medico been was walking 
and uses a crutch he is expected to be able to discard one day but 
like most head injury victims there are memories that are lost to 
him possibly forever 
an avid guitar player before the accident been found he could 
no longer play because of neurological damage to his brain like 
many head trauma victims beens brain messages misfire 
causing muscle spasticity or contraction that can severely twist 
limbs without therapy and braces 
been turned to the piano partly to relieve boredom and also 
because the physical coordination and concentration needed to play 
proved to be good therapy 
been played for some cub scouts his first christmas at new 
medico and they returned last christmas wondering if he would play 
again 
i was like christmas humbug been said i was here i 
wanna get out of here 
so they came and they touched my heart they touched my heart 
so gently he said smiling then they had me saying hey 
merry christmas 
